Generating Linux Libertine G under Linux

1. Copy Linux Libertine 5.1.3-2 sfd source directory SRC and otf/ttf Fonts to the Fonts/ subdirectory
2. Install grcompiler of SILGraphite project, ttfautohint of FreeType project and Fontforge with
   Python support
3. Create input0/, input/, output/ and hint/ directories
3. Run cpglyph.history, fontname.history and generate2:

. cpglyph.history
. fontname.history
./generate2

The results will be in the hint/.

